<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="999" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d999">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 703.4112/7.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: With reference to my
                            letter of yesterday on the subject of the chargéship of United States
                            interests in Mexico, I beg to inform you that I have this morning heard
                            from Sir L. Garden that my telegram of the 23rd of April only reached
                            him on the 29th and that he at once notified to the Minister of Foreign
                            Affairs the appointment of the Brazilian Minister, and handed over
                            American interests to the latter.</p>
                        <p>Sir L. Garden adds that it will always be a great pleasure to him to lend
                            to the Brazilian Minister any assistance in his power.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cecil Spring Rice</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>